#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A pilot project to introduce a four-day working week at companies in South Africa kicks off this year. It has already been introduced in several other countries. The idea is that employees are given 100 percent of the pay for 80 percent of the time in exchange for delivering 100 percent of the output. READ:Â UK companies to trial four-day workweek The model found less employee fatigue and higher revenue for companies. However, Herbert, Smith, Freehills Employment lawyer Jacqui Reed says while there are benefits, employers need to carefully consider the labour implications.